{"id":2273,"category_slug":"medical-english-oet","category_name":"Medical English (OET)","position":8,"title":"Test 01 - Part B - Extract 6","subtitle":"Creatinine Test Discussion","level":"B2","parts":11,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-6.2273/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-21-04-22/0-test-01-part-b-extract-6.mp3","transcript":"I can't see the results of Mr Roberts' last blood test to check creatinine levels.\nDid you do the last one?\nNo, not me... let's see...\nAh, here it is.\nThe last test was four hours ago and results show a level of 38,\nso it's still well below normal.\nWe'd better do one when he wakes up, as it might have changed.\nThe patient's not keen on needles though.\nI had a real job last night trying to convince him it was necessary.\nNot the easiest of patients, if you're happy to have a go.\nOkay... my turn, I reckon.","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:52:38","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"I can't see the results of Mr Roberts' last blood test to check creatinine levels.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-21-04-22/1.mp3","time_start":0.51,"time_end":5.66},{"position":2,"content":"Did you do the last one?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-21-04-22/2.mp3","time_start":5.66,"time_end":7.05},{"position":3,"content":"No, not me... let's see...","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-21-04-22/3.mp3","time_start":7.05,"time_end":9.88},{"position":4,"content":"Ah, here it is.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-21-04-22/4.mp3","time_start":10.29,"time_end":12.05},{"position":5,"content":"The last test was four hours ago and results show a level of 38,","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-21-04-22/5.mp3","time_start":12.05,"time_end":16.37},{"position":6,"content":"so it's still well below normal.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-21-04-22/6.mp3","time_start":16.37,"time_end":18.61},{"position":7,"content":"We'd better do one when he wakes up, as it might have changed.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-21-04-22/7.mp3","time_start":18.73,"time_end":21.84},{"position":8,"content":"The patient's not keen on needles though.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-21-04-22/8.mp3","time_start":21.84,"time_end":24.19},{"position":9,"content":"I had a real job last night trying to convince him it was necessary.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-21-04-22/9.mp3","time_start":24.19,"time_end":27.57},{"position":10,"content":"Not the easiest of patients, if you're happy to have a go.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-21-04-22/10.mp3","time_start":27.57,"time_end":31.01},{"position":11,"content":"Okay... my turn, I reckon.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/medical-english-oet/test-01-part-b-extract-6-2025-08-29-21-04-22/11.mp3","time_start":31.01,"time_end":33.45}]}